t = int(input())
for _ in range(t):
    f = list(input().split())
    s = list(input().split())
    f_set = set(f)
    s_set = set(s)
    inter = f_set.intersection(s_set)
    if len(inter) >= 2:
        print('similar')
    else:
        print('dissimilar')

import sys
for _ in range(int(sys.stdin.readline())):
    s = sys.stdin.readline().split()
    sys.stdout.write('similar\n' if len(set(s).intersection(sys.stdin.readline().split())) >= len(s) / 2 else 'dissimilar\n')

import sys
for _ in range(int(sys.stdin.readline())):
    s = list(map(str, sys.stdin.readline().split()))
    x = list(map(str, sys.stdin.readline().split()))
    sys.stdout.write('similar\n' if len(set(s).intersection(x)) >= len(s) / 2 else 'dissimilar\n')

for _ in range(int(input())):
    m = [i for i in input().split()]
    p = len([i for i in input().split() if i in m])
    print('similar' if p >= 2 else 'dissimilar')

n = int(input())
for i in range(n):
    (a, b, c, d) = input().split()
    (w, x, y, z) = input().split()
    m = []
    n = []
    m.append(a)
    m.append(b)
    m.append(c)
    m.append(d)
    n.append(w)
    n.append(x)
    n.append(y)
    n.append(z)
    c = 0
    for i in m:
        if i in n:
            c = c + 1
    if c >= 2:
        print('similar')
    else:
        print('dissimilar')

for __ in range(int(input())):
    d1 = [i for i in input().split(' ')]
    d2 = [i for i in input().split(' ')]
    s1 = set(d1)
    s2 = set(d2)
    z = s1.intersection(s2)
    x = len(s1) // 2
    y = len(z)
    if y >= x:
        print('similar')
